==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: parsec
<hw>par"sec</hw> <pr>(p⟦aum⟧r"s⟦ecr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<ets>par</ets>allax <ets>sec</ets>ond. See <er>parallax second</er> and
<cref>annual parallax</cref>, under <er>parallax</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>A unit of length used in describing
astronomical distances, equal to 3.26 light years, or 3.086 x
10<sup>13</sup> km. Abbreviated <abbr>pc</abbr>. The derived units of
kiloparsec (<abbr>kpc</abbr>, 1000 parsecs) and megaparsec
(<abbr>mpc</abbr>, one million parsecs) are often found in discussion of
astronomical distances.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parsee</ent>⟦br⟧
